<TITLE> CID arrests another ex-NSI officer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 26 (bdnews24.com)The CID has arrested former NSI deputy director major Liakat Hossain on Tuesday night in the 10-truck arms haul case in Chittagong. He was picked up from at his home in Dhanmandi in the capital, CID SSP Moniruzzaman Chowdhury told bdnews24.com. He did not give details as he was in Chittagong for investigation. Earlier on May 15, former NSI director generals retired brigadier general Abdur Rahim and retired major general Rezzakul Haider Chowdhury were arrested. They were detained on former NSI director (security) Shahab Uddin Ahmed's confession and brought to the CID office at Dampara in Chittagong on May 16 . The former chiefs were grilled in Task Force Interrogation cell. They were again taken to Chittagong on Tuesday Rahim was serving as the chief of NSI while Rezzaqul Haidar as the director of Counter Intelligence Bureau of DGFI during the arms haul. Rahim, then a retired officer, was appointed to the top NSI job by the BNP-led coalition government. Gen Chowdhury succeeded him later and was removed immediately after the army intervened to impose emergency on Jan 11, 2007. Chowdhury was also sent into retirement from the army. Shahbuddin was arrested on May 3 at his house in Dhaka on the basis of NSI field officer Akbar Hossain Khan's confession. On April 1, 2004 midnight, police had seized the 10 truckloads of arms smuggled in from the secured Chittagong Urea Fertiliser Limited jetty in Chittagong. bdnew
